date: Thu Jul 07 2022 19:07:51 GMT+1000 (Australian Eastern Standard Time)
description: Kazakhstan's first Wimbledon semi-finalist Russia-born Elena Rybakina shrugged off nerves and recovered to bulldoze her way into her first grand slam semi-final.  She fought back from a set down to beat Ajla Tomljanovic in the Wimbledon quarter-finals in three sets. The No.17 seed came from a set down and briefly entertained a stint with college tennis before deciding to turn pro, leading to her first Grand Slam semifinal. She says she wants the war in Ukraine to end “as soon as possible”.  Next she will play against Simona Halep.
